109751.name: Male:female suicide ratio
109751.description: Male:female suicide ratio is measured as the number of suicides in men versus the number in women.

source.name: Suicide rates by sex and age (IHME, 2019)
source.dataPublishedBy: Global Burden of Disease Collaborative Network. Global Burden of Disease Study 2017 (GBD 2017) Results. Seattle, United States: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation (IHME), 2018.
source.additionalInfo:
Death rates from suicide are measured as the number of suicide deaths measured per 100,000 individuals in a given demographic group.

The male-female suicide ratio is calculated by Our World in Data by dividing the male age-standardized suicide rate by the female age-standardized rate.
